    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThere are some inconsistencies between different `vim.lsp.*.enable()` functions. One of them is that some functions can enable for all buffers when given no arguments (like `inline_completion`, `linked_editing_range`, `on_type_formatting`, `codelens`), while some can not do that (`completion`, `document_color`). So for those that can't, users have to setup autocmd to enable them on some events like LspAttach\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`vim.lsp.{completion|document_color}.enable()` should enable corresponding features on all buffers with supporting LSP clients when no \"filter\" are given. So for example, if one want to enable autocompletion, they will only need one line\n```lua\nvim.lsp.completion.enable(true, nil, nil, { autotrigger = true })\n```\nFor document_color\n```lua\nvim.lsp.document_color.enable()\n```\n\n@MariaSolOs ",
